{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","content_id":"c267ed5f-e259-47ec-a4ff-c5fc5b149f11","description":"US and Canada Europe Eastern Europe and Central Asia Overseas Territories defence and international security sanctions","details":{"attends_cabinet_type":null,"body":"<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>US and Canada</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Europe</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Eastern Europe and Central Asia</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Overseas Territories</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>defence and international security</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>sanctions</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":100,"supports_historical_accounts":false,"whip_organisation":{}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","first_published_at":"2024-07-08T10:58:02+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","content_id":"c267ed5f-e259-47ec-a4ff-c5fc5b149f11","document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-26T12:16:49Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Minister of State (Europe, North America and Overseas Territories)","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","withdrawn":false}],"ordered_parent_organisations":[{"analytics_identifier":"D1315","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/foreign-commonwealth-development-office","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/foreign-commonwealth-development-office","base_path":"/government/organisations/foreign-commonwealth-development-office","content_id":"f9fcf3fe-2751-4dca-97ca-becaeceb4b26","details":{"acronym":"FCDO","brand":"foreign-commonwealth-development-office","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/621e4de4e90e0710be0354d7/s960_fcdo-main-building.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/621e4de48fa8f5490aff83b4/s300_fcdo-main-building.jpg"},"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"Foreign, Commonwealth<br/>&amp; Development Office"},"organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"live","updated_at":null,"url":null}},"document_type":"organisation","links":{},"locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/foreign-commonwealth-development-office","withdrawn":false}],"role_appointments":[{"content_id":"78cfdefc-38e0-4083-886b-7fb03406b286","details":{"current":true,"ended_on":null,"person_appointment_order":1,"started_on":"2024-07-08T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/stephen-doughty","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/stephen-doughty","base_path":"/government/people/stephen-doughty","content_id":"956b4454-bc77-4145-8c00-760140501574","details":{"body":"<p>Stephen Doughty was appointed Minister of State for Europe, North America and Overseas Territories in the Foreign, Commonwealth &amp; Development Office on 8 July 2024. Stephen was first elected as Welsh Labour and Co-operative Member of Parliament for Cardiff South and Penarth in November 2012.</p>\n\n<p>Stephen studied at Lester B. Pearson <abbr title=\"United World College\">UWC</abbr> in Canada, Oxford University and St Andrews University. He later worked for the <abbr title=\"Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe\">OSCE</abbr> Parliamentary Assembly and for members of the then National Assembly for Wales.</p>\n\n<p>Stephen spent a number of years working for humanitarian and international development <abbr title=\"non-government organisations\">NGOs</abbr> World Vision UK, Oxfam GB, Oxfam International and Oxfam Cymru. During the previous Labour government he was Special Adviser to the Secretary of State for International Development.</p>\n\n<p>Stephen served at the Wales, Home Affairs, Arms Export Controls and International Development Committees in Parliament. He was also an opposition Whip and a Shadow Minister for Trade and Industry. He chaired the All-Party Parliamentary Group for HIV and Aids, and was a member of the British-Irish Parliamentary Assembly.</p>\n\n<p>Stephen completed the Armed Forces Parliamentary scheme, attending the Royal College of Defence Studies 2017 to 2018. He has also served as an Army Reservist.</p>\n\n<p>In 2020 he was appointed Shadow Foreign Affairs and International Development Minister and in 2021 he was appointed Shadow Minister for Europe, North America and the Overseas Territories.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>Follow Stephen on X: <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://x.com/SDoughtyMP\">@SDoughtyMP</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n","image":{"alt_text":"Stephen Doughty MP","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/68d685774e830dd22fa1cec0/s465_AR109618.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-30T11:45:57Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Stephen Doughty MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/stephen-doughty","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-of-state--178","content_id":"c267ed5f-e259-47ec-a4ff-c5fc5b149f11","details":{"body":"<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>US and Canada</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Europe</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Eastern Europe and Central Asia</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Overseas Territories</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>defence and international security</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>sanctions</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":100,"whip_organisation":